# Snowflake Connection Settings for Integration Tests
# Copy this file to tests/.env and fill in your values

# ============================================================================
# REQUIRED - Connection Settings
# ============================================================================

# Your Snowflake account identifier (e.g., xy12345.us-east-1)
TEST_SNOWFLAKE_ACCOUNT=your_account_identifier

# Username to authenticate with
TEST_SNOWFLAKE_USER=your_username

# Role to use for tests (ACCOUNTADMIN recommended for full test coverage)
TEST_SNOWFLAKE_ROLE=ACCOUNTADMIN

# Warehouse for running queries
TEST_SNOWFLAKE_WAREHOUSE=COMPUTE_WH

# ============================================================================
# AUTHENTICATION - Choose ONE method
# ============================================================================

# Option 1: Key-pair authentication (RECOMMENDED)
# Generate with: openssl genrsa 2048 | openssl pkcs8 -topk8 -inform PEM -out rsa_key.p8 -nocrypt
TEST_SNOWFLAKE_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH=/path/to/your/rsa_key.p8
# If your key is encrypted with a passphrase, uncomment:
# TEST_SNOWFLAKE_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSPHRASE=your_passphrase

# Option 2: Password authentication (alternative)
# Uncomment if not using key-pair:
# TEST_SNOWFLAKE_PASSWORD=your_password

# ============================================================================
# OPTIONAL - Blueprint Variables
# ============================================================================
# Variables can be passed to blueprint configs via VAR_ prefix
# Example: VAR_MY_DATABASE=PROD_DB becomes var.my_database in YAML configs

# VAR_STORAGE_ROLE_ARN=arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/snowflake-storage-role
# VAR_STORAGE_BASE_URL=s3://my-bucket/path/
# VAR_STORAGE_AWS_EXTERNAL_ID=your-external-id

# ============================================================================
# STATIC RESOURCES
# ============================================================================
# Before running integration tests, apply static resources:
#   ./tests/fixtures/static_resources/apply.sh
#
# This creates required test infrastructure (STATIC_DATABASE, STATIC_ROLE, etc.)                                                                                   